attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Synopsys ARCv2/HS3x/HS4x cores, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib/ld-linux-arc.so.2, BuildID[sha1]=80508be75ea4f4199f45556c6d2ea3395a61b0af, for GNU/Linux 5.1.0, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a variant of the Tsunami (also known as Kaiten) IRC-based DDoS botnet. It contains clear indicators of malicious intent, including hardcoded HTTP flood templates, User-Agent spoofing strings, and function names characteristic of IRC bots (e.g., '_NICK', '_PRIVMSG', '_PING'). The presence of DDoS attack functions ('udp', 'tsunami', 'spoof') and process manipulation capabilities ('fork', 'kill', 'popen') confirms its role as a persistent backdoor and flood tool. The binary also includes strings suggesting manual spoofing configuration ('someone will have to SPOOFS me manually') and path manipulation for command execution.
